name: Babi Guling Men Janji
address: J54W+V45, Jl. Mekarsari - Baturiti Bedugul, Mekarsari, Kec. Baturiti, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82191, Indonesia
review 1: Very nice and delicious babi guling. The soup is quite spicy. The pork is soft and taste authentic. Local people loves to have lunch here. The price is also reason able. Recommended to stop and having lunch here.
review 2:
We stopped because of good reviews wanted to try traditional food babi guleng.
The staff was not speaking english and they seemed really unfriendly. They bring us some food without asking what we want to eat.
The menu was cold. We didnt like it but here it is about taste.
The problem was that both of us got digestive problems after 2-3 hoursâ€¦
review 3: Came here as per recommendation by local guide. Soup is very warm and tastes superb. Rice is mixed of red and white one. Overall my favorite is the flakes and the soup. Rest of it just so so ðŸ˜ƒ anyway they only have 1 menu, they'll serve you this one only. For 2 persons with ice sweet tea, we spent 60k.
review 4:
If you are hungry when on the way to Bedugul, you can stop and eat here.

Same as other bigul, but, in here lots of dishes and more affordable.
review 5:
Crispy pork skin and assorted pork cooked in various ways, served with soup (it's a little spicy but it's really good) and rice.

The food might look scary but it's actually delicious. The portion is huge, price is decent, cleanliness okay.
